<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-16T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-16T22:00:00-05:00" n="841" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d841">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">887N.01/1936a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Basra</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-16T23:00:00-04:00">August 16,
                                    1943—11 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>109. From Alling for Colonel Hoskins who is expected to arrive in Basra
                            about August 27th: In the interests of secrecy please do not telegraph
                            your report. Instead please send your full report by air pouch from the
                            Legation at Cairo. [Alling.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>